From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Actions-OpenWrt <actions-openwrt@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] handler: search delimiter in writable config buffer

GCC 14 warns when assigning the result of strchr(attrs[i].name, ':') to a
non-const pointer because attrs[i].name is const-qualified. The copied
configuration name in dest is the buffer that is modified below, so search
that writable buffer instead.
---
 handler.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/handler.c
+++ b/handler.c
@@ -312,7 +312,7 @@ netifd_handler_parse_config(struct uci_b
 
 		attrs[i].name = dest;
 		str_cur += sprintf(dest, "%s", name) + 1;
-		delim = strchr(attrs[i].name, ':');
+		delim = strchr(dest, ':');
 		if (delim) {
 			*delim = '\0';
 			validate[i] = ++delim;
